<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08178p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08178p">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08178p"> 178(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> after bard&apos;s song &mdash; sleep</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the earlier romances the Druids figure especially as prophets; we hear little of poets, though it is taken for granted that each division of an army has its own bards and musicians who entertain the warriors after they have eaten and before they sleep. There is no mention of judges to assist the king, and very little talk of the king as judge. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SGHI"><cite title="source">The History of Ireland</cite></a> (1923) 11</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
